"title": "8401: challenges",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8401",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God makes demands on his people and, often through spiritual leaders, confronts believers with their sin. He also calls to account false gods and those who exalt themselves against him. The wicked vainly challenge God by questioning his authority, seeking to resist his power and opposing his people.</p>\n<h2>God's challenge to his people</h2>\n<h3>The challenge to obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:15-Deut30:18\">DEU 30:15–30:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:5-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:5–19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:9\">DEU 29:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:14-Amos5:15\">AMO 5:14–5:15</a></p>\n<h3>The challenge to serve him alone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:21\">1KI 18:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:14-Josh24:15\">JOS 24:14–24:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:12-Jer3:14\">JER 3:12–3:14</a></p>\n<h3>The challenge to discipleship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24-Matt16:26\">MAT 16:24–16:26</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34-Mark8:36\">MRK 8:34–8:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23-Luke9:25\">LUK 9:23–9:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21\">MAT 19:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22\">LUK 18:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:57-Luke9:62\">LUK 9:57–9:62</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:19-Matt8:22\">MAT 8:19–8:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:17-John21:19\">JHN 21:17–21:19</a></p>\n<h2>Challenging one another's sin</h2>\n<h3>The call to rebuke and admonish</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:3\">LUK 17:3</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:17\">LEV 19:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:14\">1TH 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:14-2Thess3:15\">2TH 3:14–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:2\">2TI 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:15\">TIT 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:10\">TIT 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>Sin challenged by spiritual leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:30\">NEH 9:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:26\">NEH 9:26</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of leaders who challenged the sins of others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:1-2Sam12:7\">2SA 12:1–12:7</a> <em>The prophet Nathan challenges David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:18\">2CH 26:18</a> <em>Azariah the priest challenges Uzziah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:2\">EZK 16:2</a> <em>Ezekiel was called to confront Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:2\">HOS 2:2</a> <em>Hosea challenges the unfaithfulness of Israel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3-Acts5:4\">ACT 5:3–5:4</a> <em>Peter confronts Ananias</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:11-Gal2:14\">GAL 2:11–2:14</a> <em>Paul challenges Peter.</em></p>\n<h2>God's sovereignty is unchallengeable</h2>\n<h3>It cannot be questioned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:9-Isa45:11\">ISA 45:9–45:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:12\">JOB 9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:6\">JER 18:6</a></p>\n<h3>His purposes cannot be thwarted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:27\">ISA 14:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:2\">JOB 42:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:10\">ISA 46:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:35\">DAN 4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:21\">DAN 5:21</a></p>\n<h3>No-one can stand against him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:19\">JER 49:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:44\">JER 50:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:6\">2CH 20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:10\">JOB 41:10</a></p>\n<h2>God's challenge to the wicked</h2>\n<h3>He challenges false gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:22-1Kgs18:24\">1KI 18:22–18:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:1\">ISA 41:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:21-Isa41:23\">ISA 41:21–41:23</a></p>\n<h3>He challenges human pride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:9\">ISA 23:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:19\">ISA 13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:2\">EZK 28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:20\">DAN 5:20</a></p>\n<h2>Challenges to God and his people</h2>\n<h3>To God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:13-Isa14:14\">ISA 14:13–14:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:26-Acts4:27\">ACT 4:26–4:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:2\">PSA 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:4-Gen3:5\">GEN 3:4–3:5</a> <em>The serpent challenges God's word</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:19\">ISA 5:19</a> <em>Isaiah's opponents challenge God to do what he has announced.</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:36\">DAN 11:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:4\">2TH 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:5-Rev13:6\">REV 13:5–13:6</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1\">MAT 4:1</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:12-Mark1:13\">MRK 1:12–1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:2\">LUK 4:1–4:2</a> <em>Jesus Christ is tempted by the devil</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:22\">MAT 16:22</a> <em>Jesus Christ is challenged by Peter</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:13\">JHN 8:13</a> <em>the Pharisees challenge Jesus Christ</em></p>\n<h3>To God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:8-1Sam17:11\">1SA 17:8–17:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:10\">PSA 42:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:3\">PSA 42:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:10\">PSA 79:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:25\">DAN 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:11\">DAN 8:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:17\">JOL 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:10-Eph6:12\">EPH 6:10–6:12</a> <em>God's people are equipped to stand against the devil's attacks</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:7\">REV 13:7</a></p>\n<h2>Further examples of challenges</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:4\">JDG 14:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:8\">2KI 14:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:17\">2CH 25:17</a></p>",
